			},
					3182: {
				id_comment: 3182,
				source_str: '✻',
				caption: '',
				content: "vv. 3-5: The simplest explanation of these verses is that St Paul did have Titus circumcised, but not because anybody insisted on it, only so as to avoid giving any scandal to the Judaizing brethren. (Cf. Ac. 16.3, where the phrase used is exactly the same.) It was not (he adds in verse 5) by way of obedience to any demands from them, as the Galatians had perhaps been told. Other commentators reject this idea as inconsistent with St Paul’s principles, and explain that St Paul forgot to finish the sentence he began in verse 4."
			},
					3183: {
